    library(tidyverse)

    # Create bins (low/high) for Age and YearsWithCompany based on median
    data <- data %>%
      mutate(
        AgeGroup = ifelse(Age <= median(Age, na.rm = TRUE), "Low Age", "High Age"),
        TenureGroup = ifelse(YearsAtCompany <= median(YearsAtCompany, na.rm = TRUE), 
                             "Low Tenure", "High Tenure")
      )

    # Calculate attrition proportion for each group combination
    attrition_summary <- data %>%
      group_by(AgeGroup, TenureGroup) %>%
      summarise(
        Total = n(),
        AttritionYes = sum(Attrition == "Yes"),
        AttritionRate = round(100 * AttritionYes / Total, 1)
      )

    ## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'AgeGroup'. You can override using the
    ## `.groups` argument.

    print(attrition_summary)

    ## # A tibble: 4 × 5
    ## # Groups:   AgeGroup [2]
    ##   AgeGroup TenureGroup Total AttritionYes AttritionRate
    ##   <chr>    <chr>       <int>        <int>         <dbl>
    ## 1 High Age High Tenure   232           20           8.6
    ## 2 High Age Low Tenure    199           26          13.1
    ## 3 Low Age  High Tenure   182           23          12.6
    ## 4 Low Age  Low Tenure    257           71          27.6

    # Plot the proportion of attrition
    ggplot(attrition_summary, aes(x = AgeGroup, y = AttritionRate, fill = TenureGroup)) +
      geom_bar(stat = "identity", position = position_dodge(width = 0.7), width = 0.6) +
      geom_text(aes(label = paste0(AttritionRate, "%")), 
                position = position_dodge(width = 0.7), vjust = -0.2, size = 4.2) +
      scale_fill_manual(values = c("#A50021", "#e8e8e8")) +
      labs(title = "Attrition Rate by Age and Tenure Groups",
           x = "Age Group", y = "Attrition Rate (%)", fill = "Tenure Group") +
      theme_minimal(base_size = 13) +
      theme(
        plot.title = element_text(color = "#A50021", face = "bold", hjust = 0.5),
        legend.position = "top"
      )

    library(tidyverse)

    # Create distance bins (using quantiles or custom cut points)
    data <- data %>%
      mutate(DistanceGroup = case_when(
        DistanceFromHome <= 5  ~ "Short (≤5 km)",
        DistanceFromHome <= 10 ~ "Medium (6–10 km)",
        TRUE                   ~ "Long (>10 km)"
      ))

    # Calculate attrition rate by distance group
    attrition_distance <- data %>%
      group_by(DistanceGroup) %>%
      summarise(
        Total = n(),
        AttritionYes = sum(Attrition == "Yes"),
        AttritionRate = round(100 * AttritionYes / Total, 1)

    # NAIVE BAYES MODEL
    # ==========================================================
    # 1️⃣ Load Required Libraries
    # ==========================================================
    required_packages <- c("tidyverse", "caret", "smotefamily", "e1071")
    for (pkg in required_packages) {
      if (!requireNamespace(pkg, quietly = TRUE))
        install.packages(pkg, dependencies = TRUE)
      library(pkg, character.only = TRUE)
    }

    ## Loading required package: lattice

    ## 
    ## Attaching package: 'caret'

    ## The following object is masked from 'package:purrr':
    ## 
    ##     lift

    # ==========================================================
    # 2️⃣ Prepare Dataset
    # ==========================================================
    data$AttritionFlag <- factor(ifelse(data$Attrition == "Yes", "Yes", "No"),
                                 levels = c("No", "Yes"))  # "No" = stayed (positive)

    selected_features <- c(
      "JobInvolvement", "TotalWorkingYears", "JobLevel",
      "YearsInCurrentRole", "MonthlyIncome", "Age",
      "StockOptionLevel", "YearsWithCurrManager",
      "YearsAtCompany", "JobSatisfaction"
    )

    model_data <- data %>% select(all_of(selected_features), AttritionFlag)

    # ==========================================================
    # 3️⃣ Split Data (70% Train, 30% Test)
    # ==========================================================
    set.seed(70)
    train_index <- createDataPartition(model_data$AttritionFlag, p = 0.7, list = FALSE)
    train_data <- model_data[train_index, ]
    test_data  <- model_data[-train_index, ]

    cat("\nClass distribution in Training Set:\n")

    ##

    print(table(train_data$AttritionFlag))

    ##

    ## Class distribution in Test Set:

    print(table(test_data$AttritionFlag))

    ## 
    ##  No Yes 
    ## 219  42

    # ==========================================================
    # 4️⃣ Cross-Validation Setup (Repeated CV with SMOTE)
    # ==========================================================
    train_ctrl <- trainControl(
      method = "repeatedcv",
      number = 20,
      repeats = 10,
      sampling = "smote",          # SMOTE applied inside each fold
      classProbs = TRUE,
      savePredictions = "final",
      summaryFunction = twoClassSummary
    )

    # ==========================================================
    # 5️⃣ Train Naive Bayes Model (No Scaling)
    # ==========================================================
    set.seed(70)
    nb_model_cv <- train(
      AttritionFlag ~ .,
      data = train_data,
      method = "naive_bayes",
      trControl = train_ctrl,
      metric = "ROC"
    )

    model_data <- data %>% select(all_of(selected_features), AttritionFlag)

    # Store good seeds
    good_seeds <- data.frame(
      Seed = integer(),
      AUC = numeric(),
      Sensitivity = numeric(),
      Specificity = numeric()
    )

    # Loop over seeds
    for (s in 1:100) {
      set.seed(s)
      train_index <- createDataPartition(model_data$AttritionFlag, p = 0.7, list = FALSE)
      train_data <- model_data[train_index, ]
      test_data  <- model_data[-train_index, ]

      train_ctrl <- trainControl(
        method = "repeatedcv",
        number = 10,
        repeats = 3,
        sampling = "smote",
        classProbs = TRUE,
        savePredictions = "final",
        summaryFunction = twoClassSummary
      )

      tune_grid <- expand.grid(k = seq(3, 15, 2))

      set.seed(s)
      knn_model_cv <- train(
        AttritionFlag ~ .,
        data = train_data,
        method = "knn",
        trControl = train_ctrl,
        preProcess = c("center", "scale"),
        tuneGrid = tune_grid,
        metric = "ROC"
      )

      cv_results <- knn_model_cv$resample %>%
        summarise(
          AUC = mean(ROC, na.rm = TRUE) * 100,
          Sensitivity = mean(Sens, na.rm = TRUE) * 100,
          Specificity = mean(Spec, na.rm = TRUE) * 100
        ) %>%
        round(2)

      if (cv_results$Sensitivity > 60 & cv_results$Specificity > 60) {
        good_seeds <- rbind(good_seeds, cbind(Seed = s, cv_results))
      }
    }

    cat("\n✅ Seeds with Sensitivity & Specificity > 60%:\n")

    ## 
    ## ✅ Seeds with Sensitivity & Specificity > 60%:

    print(good_seeds)
